  <h1>
   application_surface
  </h1>
  This global, built-in variable can be used to access the application surface, for use in any of the
  <a href="Surfaces.htm">
   surface functions
  </a>
  . This surface is permanently available and is where the game is drawn by
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  .
  
  
   The regular Draw events (
  <em>
   Draw Begin
  </em>
  ,
  <em>
   Draw
  </em>
  and
  <em>
   Draw End
  </em>
  ) draw to this surface by default. Other Draw events (like
  <em>
   Pre/Post Draw
  </em>
  and
  <em>
   Draw GUI
  </em>
  ) do not draw on the application surface. See
  <a href="../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Object_Properties/Draw_Events.htm">
   Draw Events
  </a>
  for more information on how those events work.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">application_surface;
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Drawing/Surfaces/surface_create.htm">
 Surface ID
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">surface_resize(application_surface, display_get_gui_width(), display_get_gui_height())
</code></pre>
  The above code will resize the application surface to have a 1:1 ratio with the GUI layer.
 </body>
